oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Clean-up Crew and Equipment Following Masonic Building Collapse, 1949
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a man driving a large piece of machinery up to the collapsed Masonic Building in downtown Clarksville to aid in the clean-up efforts after the building collapsed.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Building failures; Construction equipment; Freemasonry--Lodges
